@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnThemedPanelRazor — Phase 7.1 Gate 2 TRANSITIONAL TWIN of BnThemedPanel
    (BnDemo's demo-internal cascading consumer): reads the cascaded BnTheme
    and renders a BnView with the theme's current background — the "themed
    child" whose re-render on theme change is DoD #6's proof surface. At
    swap time this file is `git mv`ed to BnThemedPanel.razor and the
    hand-written internal class (declared in BnDemo.cs) retires with BnDemo.

    VISIBILITY CHANGE, FORCED AND RECORDED: the hand-written panel was
    `internal`. The Razor compiler's component discovery only considers
    PUBLIC types — an internal component in markup silently parses as a
    plain HTML element (an unknown-element wire violation the twin test
    would catch loudly) — and the generated class is `public partial` with
    no way to narrow it. So converting BnDemo to .razor REQUIRES the panel
    to go public; given that, authoring the panel itself in .razor is the
    cleaner half of the same decision. Pre-1.0 surface addition, recorded
    for the phase conclusion.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnView BackgroundColor="@(Theme?.Background)" Padding="@Padding" ChildContent="@ChildContent" />

@code {
    /// <summary>The cascaded theme (see BnTheme: a NEW record instance per
    /// toggle is what makes CascadingValue notify its consumers).</summary>
    [CascadingParameter] public BnTheme? Theme { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Padding"/>
    [Parameter] public float? Padding { get; set; }

    /// <summary>Nested content rendered inside the themed view.</summary>
    [Parameter] public RenderFragment? ChildContent { get; set; }
}
